  "groups": [
    {
      "id": "group-1",
      "name": "Table memory",
      "nodeIds": [
        "trigger-cadence",
        "trigger-state",
        "mode",
        "maintain",
        "log-apply"
      ],
      "collapsed": true,
      "exposed": [
        {
          "node": "mode",
          "path": "selected",
          "label": "Mode"
        },
        {
          "node": "trigger-cadence",
          "path": "everyNFloors",
          "label": "Cadence (floors)"
        },
        {
          "node": "trigger-state",
          "path": "value",
          "label": "Backlog threshold"
        },
        {
          "node": "maintain",
          "path": "api_preset_id",
          "label": "API preset"
        }
      ],
      "note": "Setup needed before turning memory on: bind a table template with a 'summary' table in the Tables view (the backlog trigger watches summary.unprocessed), and optionally set an API preset on the Memory node so maintenance runs on a cheaper connection. Edit each table's maintenance rules in the Memory node's panel. Modes: every_turn = maintain every N floors; async = maintain when the un-summarized backlog reaches the threshold; off = memory maintenance disabled."
    }
  ]
